commission has an enduring impact

00:40:04.490 --> 00:40:08.060
upon what it means to be
Cherokee in the 21st century.

00:40:08.060 --> 00:40:12.730
This is the commission
as I detail in the book

00:40:12.730 --> 00:40:18.130
which separates families
based upon race,

00:40:18.130 --> 00:40:22.920
ethnicity, language, and culture.

00:40:22.920 --> 00:40:25.060
There are some really
quite heartbreaking stories

00:40:25.060 --> 00:40:30.020
of Cherokee Citizenship
Commission as using their positions

00:40:30.020 --> 00:40:35.110
for political reasons to
punish political opponents.

00:40:35.110 --> 00:40:37.120
Now this is not uniquely Cherokee.

00:40:37.120 --> 00:40:41.450
This is something that
is very human, I think,

00:40:41.450 --> 00:40:44.470
in a modern context
to do such things.

00:40:44.470 --> 00:40:47.090
But nonetheless, many of
the stories that emerged

00:40:47.090 --> 00:40:50.250
out of the Cherokee citizenship
commission are really quite fraught

00:40:50.250 --> 00:40:54.110
and for African-American
people in particular.

00:40:54.110 --> 00:40:58.850
The Cherokee Citizenship Commission
is something of a disaster

00:40:58.850 --> 00:41:03.940
for many thousands of people
who by genealogy and by virtue

00:41:03.940 --> 00:41:08.080
of their ancestors being
enslaved by Cherokee slaveholders

00:41:08.080 --> 00:41:11.650
